definitions.definition: A peninsula in Greece , separated from mainland Europe by the Gulf of Corinth and connected to it by the Isthmus of Corinth .
A periphery of Greece containing Achaea , Arcadia , Argolis , Corinthia , Elis , Laconia , and Messenia .
